ng an organizational identity that downplayed class struggle and embraced discipline, peaceful solutions to labor market problems, and cooperation with the employers. As Jansson shows, study activities arranged by the Workers' Educational Association became the main tool of the Trade Union Confederation's identity policy in the 1920s and 1930s and its successful outcome paved the way for the well-known "Swedish Model."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aLabor movementzSwedenxHistoryy20th century. 0aWorking classzSwedenxHistoryy20th century. 4aBusiness (General). 4aEducation & History Of Education. 4aLabor History. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Labor & Industrial Relations.2bisacsh  aSweden, Class formation, Labor leaders, Trade union movement, Identity entrepreneurs.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCOR eBook-Package Pilot Project 2020z978311069046008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2020z9783110704594oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150175003840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501750038423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501750038.jpg  a978-3-11-069046-0  COR eBook-Package Pilot Project 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070472-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishb2020  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPD